  "body": "That PR https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/14249 implemented formatting selection natively for the text input on Android. However, it seems to be not stable. On my device (Samsung galaxy note 10 lite - Android 11), after pressing \"BIU\" nothing happens (most of the time).\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n1. Open a chat.\r\n2. Type some text and select it.\r\n3. Select \"BIU\"\r\n\r\nExpected behaviour: Bold, Italic, Strikethrough should appear like in the designs https://www.figma.com/file/wA8Epdki2OWa8Vr067PCNQ/Composer-for-Mobile?node-id=2630%3A212161&t=amRskTi8EB8gB4wY-0\r\n\r\nCurrent behaviour: nothing happens (I was able to see the menu appearing one time only)\r\n\r\nOn iOS, it is not yet implemented.",
